# Domain: Builder Templates

Per core invariants and domain-builder. Builder templates define **structure only** (block types and labels); they do not store block content. Application is pure state transformation.

## Template Application

- **useTemplateApplication:** Accepts `desktopList` and `mobileList` refs. `applyTemplate(templateId, screen)` gets template from store, builds new block items with unique IDs, **replaces** the target list ref value(s). No `push`, `splice`, or in-place mutation of the list.
- **Unique block IDs:** Each application generates new IDs (e.g. `{type}-{timestamp}-{uuid}`). Do not reuse IDs from a previous list or template.

## No One-Off Logic

- **Templates are compositional.** Template definitions are data (id, name, description, category, blocks array). No special-case or one-off logic in the application flow for a single template; all templates go through the same apply path.
- **Block items** are `{ id, type, label }`. No embedding of custom content in template definitions; content comes from blocks store after blocks are created.

## Store and Components

- **stores/templates.ts:** Holds template definitions and exposes getters (e.g. by id, by category). No duplicate list of templates elsewhere.
- **TemplatesList.vue:** Presents templates and emits apply with templateId and screen. Does not hold template state; reads from store via composable or store.

Reference `docs/07-TEMPLATE-SYSTEM.md` for APIs and patterns.
